def: Among the Jews, penetrating investigation, disputation, anddrawing of conclusions, esp. in Talmudic study. -- Pil"pul*ist (#),n. --Pil`pul*is"tic (#), a.
In the smooth and melodious style of an air; ariose.
A servant who has charge of the dairy; a dairymaid. [Obs.]Chaucer.
Having many angles. Polygonal numbers, certain figuratenumbers. See under Figurate.
The quality or state of being reparable.
A tribe of Indians which formerly occupied the region ofNorthern Illinois, allied in language to the Sacs and Foxes.
